"Maione M., Arduini J., Mangani G., Geniali A.","Evaluation of an automatic sampling gas chromatographic-mass spectrometric instrument for continuous monitoring of trace anthropogenic gases",2004,"International Journal of Environmental Analytical Chemistry","84","4",,"241","253",,,10.1080/03067310310001626740,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-1842588942&partnerID=40&md5=3060e453b14b0df7044074e820c83c04","Univ. degli Studi di Urbino, Istituto di Scienze Chimiche, Piazza Rinascimento 6, 61029 Urbino, Italy","Maione, M., Univ. degli Studi di Urbino, Istituto di Scienze Chimiche, Piazza Rinascimento 6, 61029 Urbino, Italy; Arduini, J., Univ. degli Studi di Urbino, Istituto di Scienze Chimiche, Piazza Rinascimento 6, 61029 Urbino, Italy; Mangani, G., Univ. degli Studi di Urbino, Istituto di Scienze Chimiche, Piazza Rinascimento 6, 61029 Urbino, Italy; Geniali, A., Univ. degli Studi di Urbino, Istituto di Scienze Chimiche, Piazza Rinascimento 6, 61029 Urbino, Italy","Continuous monitoring of the atmospheric volatile halogenated hydrocarbons is needed in light of the role played by these compounds in global climate change phenomena. The analytical methodology described in the following implies the use of a gas chromatographic-mass spectrometric system equipped with a sampling/pre-concentration unit, for the simultaneous and continuous analysis of a number of halogenated hydrocarbons present in the atmosphere at concentration levels ranging from a few to hundreds of part per trillion by volume. The optimization of the analytical procedure in terms of efficiency, linearity, and reproducibility is reported together with some of the results obtained in the frame of a monitoring activity carried out on a remote mountain station in central Italy.","CFCs; Continuous monitoring; GC-MS; Greenhouse gases; Halocarbons","Climate change; Gas chromatography; Gases; Hydrocarbons; Trace analysis; Halogenated hydrocarbons; Reproducibility; Mass spectrometry",,,,,,"Wallington, T.J., Schneider, W.F., Worsnop, D.R., Nielsen, O.J., Sehested, J., Debruyn, W.J., Shorter, J.A., (1994) Environ. Sci. Technol, 28, pp. 320-326; Pinnock, S., Hurley, M.H., Shine, K.P., Wallington, T.J., Smyth, T.J., (1995) J. Geophys. Res, 100 (D11), p. 23; (1987) Montreal Protocol to Reduce Substances That Deplete the Ozone Layer, Final Report, , UN Environmental Programme, New York; (1994) Report of the Fourth Meeting of the Parties to the Montreal Protocol on Substances That Deplete the Ozone Layer, , Copenhagen Amendment to the Montreal Protocol. UNEP (United Nations Environment Programme) 1992. United Nations, New York; Simmonds, P.G., Derewent, R.G., McCulloch, A., O'Doherty, S., Gaudry, A., (1996) Atmos. Environ., 30, pp. 4041-4063; Derewent, R.G., Simmonds, P.G., O'Doherty, S., Ciais, P., Ryall, D.B., (1998) Atmos. Environ., 32, pp. 3703-3715; Derewent, R.G., Simmonds, P.G., O'Doherty, S., Ryall, D.B., (1998) Atmos. Environ., 32, pp. 3689-3702; Mangani, F., Maione, M., Lattanzi, L., Arduini, J., (2000) Atmos. Environ., 34, pp. 5303-5309; Oram, D.E., Reeves, C.E., Penkett, S.A., Fraser, P.J., (1995) Geophys. Res. Lett., 22, pp. 2741-2744; Montzka, A., Butler, J.H., Myers, R.C., Thompson, T.M., Swanson, T.H., Clarke, A.D., Lock, L.T., Elkin, J.W., (1996) Science, 272, pp. 1318-1322; Montzka, S.A., Myers, R.C., Butler, J.H., Elkins, J.W., Lock, L.T., Clarke, A.D., Goldstein, A.H., (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, pp. 169-172; Oram, D.E., Reeves, C.E., Sturges, W.T., Penkett, S.A., Fraser, P.J., Lagenfelds, R.L., (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, pp. 1949-1952; Montzka, S.A., Butler, J.H., Elkins, J.W., Thompson, T.M., Clarke, A.D., Lock, L.T., (1999) Nature, 398, pp. 690-693; Sturges, W.T., Elkins, J.W., (1993) J. Chromatogr., 642, pp. 123-134; Simmonds, P.G., O'Doherthy, S., Nickless, G., Sturrock, G.A., Swany, R., Knight, P., Ricketts, J., Smith, R., (1995) Anal. Chem., 67, pp. 717-723; Armstrong, D.W., Reid, G.L., Gasper III, M.P., (1996) J. Microcolumn Sep